      public void onPartAddClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException

    • onProductAddSaveClick

      public void onProductAddSaveClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent) throws IOException
      This method take information from text fields and partsList and uses them to generate a new product, with appropriate exceptions being thrown when fields are filled in incorrectly. This method invokes windowloader method in order to return to previous window.

      LOGIC ERROR - I had 'if (min > max)', which needed to be corrected as it allowed min and max to be the same number, which would not make sense.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - The actionEvent generated by the Save button being clicked.
      Throws:
      IOException

    • getPartsResultHandler1

      public void getPartsResultHandler1(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      This method allows users to search for parts in Inventories allParts list, and searches for a parts name (or partial name) and ID.

      LOGIC ERROR - I had to use Scanner function in order to properly determine if there was an integer in the searchText, as otherwise my Exception message was not loading properly.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - This actionEvent is generated by searching (i.e. hitting Return / Enter) in the search bar.

    • onRemoveAssociatedPartClick

      public void onRemoveAssociatedPartClick(javafx.event.ActionEvent actionEvent)
      This method removes part from partsList. Confirmation is needed to remove part.
      Parameters:
      actionEvent - This actionEvent is initiated by clicking Remove button.
